    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase statutory maternity pay to 80% to match the current furlough scheme",
        "additional_details": "Staff furloughed to look after children are currently receiving 80% of their salary up to \u00a32500. Staff receiving statutory maternity, paternity or adoption leave are receiving \u00a3148.68 a week, many of which do not receive any enhancement from their employer. In fairness this should be increased while the furlough scheme is running.",
        "background": "Increase statutory maternity, paternity and adoption pay to 80% to run along side the current furlough scheme due to Covid-19.",
